"""Task modules for {{ project_name }}.

Each task is a Python module with a standard interface. train.py and
eval.py load the task based on the ``task`` config key and assemble
the Trainer/Evaluator automatically.

Required (preprocessing):
    preprocess(cfg) -> None                  # raw data → processed data

Required (training + eval):
    build_dataloader(cfg, split="train", fold=None) -> DataLoader
    build_model(cfg) -> nn.Module

Required (training):
    make_compute_loss(cfg) -> Callable[[nn.Module, batch], Tensor]
    make_evaluate(cfg) -> Callable           # train-time validation (fast)

Required (eval):
    make_test_evaluate(cfg) -> Callable      # post-training eval (thorough)

Optional overrides:
    build_optimizer(model, cfg) -> Optimizer       # default: AdamW
    build_scheduler(optimizer, cfg) -> LRScheduler # default: cosine + warmup
    build_eval_callbacks(cfg) -> list[EvalCallback]
    on_complete(cfg, fold_results) -> None         # sequential CV post-hook
    run(cfg) -> None                               # full training loop override
    evaluate(cfg) -> None                          # full eval loop override

Usage:
    make train TRAIN_ARGS="task=example training.epochs=5"
    make eval EVAL_ARGS="task=example"
"""
